## Testing Child ViewModels

Each child ViewModel should be **independently testable** with mocked services. Parent orchestration logic should be minimal and unit-tested separately.

```csharp
var mockService = new Mock<IMyService>();
mockService.Setup(x => x.DoWorkAsync()).ReturnsAsync(result);

var vm = new MyViewModel(mockService.Object);
await vm.DoCommand.ExecuteAsync(null);

Assert.Equal(expectedState, vm.State);
```

---

## XML Documentation

Add **XML docs** to public ViewModels and public properties with non-obvious purpose. Do not document every property; comment only when behavior is unclear.

```csharp
/// <summary>
/// Orchestrates the session page, switching between the new session form and active session display.
/// </summary>
public partial class SessionPageViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    /// <summary>
    /// The form for starting a new session. Communicates completion via the <see cref="OnSessionStarted"/> callback.
    /// </summary>
    public NewSessionViewModel NewSession { get; }
}
```

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Each ViewModel is **< ~150 lines**; complex features are split into child ViewModels or services.
- [ ] State is managed via **state records** (not scattered booleans).
- [ ] **No visibility-only properties**; use computed properties or converters instead.
- [ ] **State transitions are semantic**: Multi-property updates grouped into intent-driven methods (`ShowLoadingState()`, not `UpdateUI()`).
- [ ] Commands are **verb-driven** and have clear `CanExecute` predicates.
- [ ] Complex logic is **delegated to services**.
- [ ] Child ViewModels use **callbacks** (not events) for parent communication.
- [ ] Async methods are **suffixed with `Async`** and handle exceptions.
- [ ] Each child ViewModel is **independently testable**.
- [ ] Public API has **XML docs**; no emojis in comments.
